column5: I need a place to stay between Cloque and International Falls. I'm late in checking and most of the national chains are booked up any suggestions on a Ma & Pa type place?
[font color=green size=3][b]The Super 8 in International Falls is seldom booked full, and the desk is open all night it's right on Hwy 53. I'll probably be pulling in there tonight about 1AM.
What cities/towns are in that path?
The Super 8 was full but I found the last two rooms in northern Mn.
for an inexpensive night in a plain motel, try Andersons in Orr, MN

What ever you do stay away from the Super 8 in Ft. Francis, if there's a bigger motel rip-off in Canada I like to know where! We got scalped to the tune of $120 (American) a room for three rooms on a thursday night last year.
Hi. we allways stay at the black bear casino going up and coming back.
